                <head>319. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On November 16, representatives of the United States and Brazil signed a Surplus
                    Agricultural Agreement under the provisions of Title I of Public Law 480. Under
                    the terms of the agreement, the United States agreed to sell to Brazil surplus
                    agricultural commodities valued at approximately $41 million. For text of the
                    agreement, signed at Rio de Janeiro, see 6 UST 4033. Considerable additional
                    documentation concerning the negotiation of this agreement is in Department of
                    State, Central File 411.3241.</p>
            </div>
